</title>
<subSubSection id="41BE089494937C8BB973DE6FB8838DE2" pageId="null" pageNumber="575" type="description">
<paragraph id="6BBAB68C1C6777D831118C4861D034FA" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="9B0F8D5E1A660F896B88086B667D957F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="575" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="halleri">
<emphasis id="75F2724D67A68C5F940829B5D4BC1929" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Ch. Halleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 9g) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="47028BC27C2852CB807CDE6A9127FEDC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">20</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="0497100B368B34C0F93FB4FEDE5E8359" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">
40 cm hoch; 
<normalizedToken id="D0298E8026E52D4B891F3075CC53577A" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
stets jederseits bis 
<normalizedToken id="C4009EF8D80E198FA47C7055440940D8" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">ueber</normalizedToken>
die Mitte fiederteilig, Zipfel
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="C0A0BDACFFBF072E4582F27465E8C9DF" originalValue="1½" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">11/2</normalizedToken>
- 
<emphasis id="EE8AFBF15355FC3F12CFFB1EDA07B6A0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">
3mal so lang wie die ungeteilte Blattmitte; oberhalb der Stengelmitte meist keine 
<normalizedToken id="D445185FFC20B14BC5127E5F82F78C0B" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
mehr;
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="33E483524B889206C7623B5EBCFAD741" originalValue="Köpfe" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Koepfe</normalizedToken>
im Durchmesser 4,5-6,5 cm. - 
<normalizedToken id="5E59CEDD5C747DB0FD631926F4AD0B2B" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer und 
<normalizedToken id="4E560B9FC4B82C4E317FBA4AE994BA9C" originalValue="früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">frueher</normalizedToken>
Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A79E9E0E567FD239ECB3AB2D620FAD91" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="AAEE2A1D36E397A460CF84F86FA0D060" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="49E84D693C45BE1F9D1BDD71A39243F0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">54:</emphasis>
Material von verschiedenen Stellen aus den 
<normalizedToken id="C9B002419BFFDA307CC2E23EBD62E643" originalValue="Südwestalpen" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Suedwestalpen</normalizedToken>
(Villard 1968).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE1DB0386C865B919D780C586D8182E1" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="3AB021146624BAAC34366EA8C04A7B08" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Standort.</emphasis>
Subalpin und alpin. 
<normalizedToken id="11B1CB4B99CD0652C50AC119A63F1D9F" originalValue="Ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Aehnlich</normalizedToken>
wie 
<taxonomicName id="5D26256B8AC638E49A4C6F9AD7F91746" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="575" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="halleri">
<emphasis id="388A00043515B05356C1A2D2054F5B19" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Ch. Halleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 9g).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="456E360D0FFF60B525716E94D89FA4F0" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="30685DCC08FFDD5BD942103ED8433E38" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">
<pageBreakToken id="6F0986BBC8F72097C59D6D9D99A6FEA7" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Verbreitung</pageBreakToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="0AB27AF2529F0EAE38A3D30A0A6E9A73" originalValue="Südwestalpen-Pflanze" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Suedwestalpen-Pflanze</normalizedToken>
:
</emphasis>
Von den Alpes Maritimes 
<normalizedToken id="1F836D192E540CA046C745C8CDBA2FC8" originalValue="nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis 
<normalizedToken id="B1BF75E0E4DBA7B706D09DDBCC72ADA1" originalValue="südliches" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">suedliches</normalizedToken>
Savoyen. - Im Gebiet: Savoyen (Gegend des Mont Cenis und des Col du Clapier).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F5AC67E7FC43717748900EB21181E47" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="BE93FFC3236294B8EFB345E878A21815" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Das nahe verwandte 
<taxonomicName id="ADCEAFA99BA28783B3FC3F71DB439747" authority="All." authorityName="All." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="575" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ceratophylloides">
<emphasis id="740A918AE22F3C80B604E94791384BF6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Ch. ceratophylloides</emphasis>
All.
</taxonomicName>
besitzt die gleiche Chromosomenzahl (Favarger und Villard 1965, Villard 1968) und hat eine 
<normalizedToken id="D4AFCF53399F394408C4FB4F80F8F77A" originalValue="südlichere" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">suedlichere</normalizedToken>
Verbreitung in den 
<normalizedToken id="24832C5676A7861E4DD172D3F559CCE4" originalValue="Südwestalpen" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Suedwestalpen</normalizedToken>
. Es besitzt noch tiefer geteilte 
<normalizedToken id="8118B4AE758C6AA4BA5539243389E842" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
und ist mit 
<taxonomicName id="86EE4640874AFBA0E9BD2CBCA9F7D8DA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="575" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronopifolium">
<emphasis id="06200AC6D734E5810E697879CA80EA99" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Ch. coronopifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
durch 
<normalizedToken id="C05FC48E66F652D40FEE52B5D3805357" originalValue="Übergänge" pageId="null" pageNumber="575">Uebergaenge</normalizedToken>
verbunden.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
